        "notesStmt": {
          "note": [
            "Ms. codex.",
            "Title from caption title (f. 1v).",
            "An owner's stamp and note (f. 1r). The name in the note is Jān Sipār Khān ibn Rustamdilkhān ibn Jān Sipār Khān al-Ḥusaynī al-Mukhtār al-Sabzawārī; the note also mentions that this was a gift from Nawwāb Ṣāḥib Qiblah Nawwāb Mukhtār Khān in the year 1122 A.H. (1710 CE). The name in the seal is the same, with a different formulation: Jān Sipār Khān, Khānahʹzād-i Shah-i ʻĀlam Pādishāh Muʻaẓẓam Pādishāh-i Ghāzī, 1121 A.H., year 3.",
            "Typwritten note in purple ink pasted in: \"A specimen of fine calligraphy with seal of Emperor Aurangzeb\" (f. 12v)."
          ]
        },
